title: Bug 110566: Wrong data set result returned when an invalid filter expression is set for row[0]
description: When setting a filter expression like 'row[0] equals to 0', the data set result is incorrect or null.
OB: The data set result is incorrect or null when the filter expression 'row[0] equals to 0' is set.
EB: A relevant error message should pop up when an invalid filter expression like 'row[0] equals to 0' is set.
SR:
To reproduce the issue:
1. Open the application.
2. Navigate to the data set filter settings.
3. Set the filter expression 'row[0] equals to 0'.
4. Verify the resulting data set.
